fieldNotes: Recorded using LG Optimus smartphone.  The bird was heard singing multiple times in a large valley in Mudeungsan National Park.  I was finally able to locate the bird near a small mountain stream; despite being directly under it at one point, I was not able to visually locate the bird.  The habitat was mountain forest, primarily deciduous with some evergreen.  A shallow, medium-flowing mountain stream was nearby; lots of canopy cover with some knee-height underbrush.  I do not know how many records of fairy pitta exist for the Gwangju area, but this species should be considered quite rare for this location, and was truly an unexpected surprise to come across.; animal seen:no; playback used:no
